{
  "text": "For both plots the C p values for the materials were determined from their m values through the correlation m = 20.7 C p discussed in Stevenson and Wolynes [CITATION_1] . Maximal compactness implies a roughly spherical shape giving a free-energy cost",
  "correct_citation": {
